<section xml:id="sec_1_2_examples" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Examples</title>
  <exercises>

        <introduction>
          <p>
            Disc golf is a sport that contains of three types of frisbees: drivers, midranges, and putters. Some disc golfer's bag contains 6 drivers, 5 midranges, and 3 putters.
          </p>
        </introduction>

        <exercise>
          <statement>
            <p>
              How many permutations of this bag can you make?
            </p>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <p>
              There are <m> 14! </m> permutations of this bag which is equivalent to <m> 87,178,291,200 </m>
            </p>
          </solution>
        </exercise>

        <exercise>
          <statement>
            <p>
              This disc golfer's friend challenges him to play a hole with three random discs from his bag in the order in which he picks them. How many permuations could the friend make?
            </p>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <p>
              There are <m> \frac{14!}{(14-3)!} </m> which is equivalent to <m> 2184 </m>
            </p>
          </solution>
        </exercise>

    </exercises>
</section>
